to clean your carpets...

309
00:15:18,308 --> 00:15:19,358
Here.

310
00:15:21,298 --> 00:15:22,185
I dreamt this.

311
00:15:22,265 --> 00:15:23,621
I dreamt this whole morning.

312
00:15:23,785 --> 00:15:25,985
Everything-- the juice,
the phone call,

313
00:15:26,474 --> 00:15:28,640
Ariel wanting to stay
home from school.

314
00:15:29,091 --> 00:15:30,706
Uh, okay. So?

315
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:31,881
Everything.

316
00:15:32,275 --> 00:15:34,223
It's as if I lived
this day already.

317
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,059
And I'm gonna get in a horrible
car accident in a little while.

318
00:15:38,511 --> 00:15:39,272
You're what?

319
00:15:39,378 --> 00:15:40,511
No, wait, wait.

320
00:15:41,531 --> 00:15:43,292
I had that dream for a reason.

321
00:15:44,106 --> 00:15:45,794
I can stop this from happening.

322
00:15:51,136 --> 00:15:52,028
Hello.

323
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:53,559
Good morning, yeah.

324
00:15:53,622 --> 00:15:55,532
Is Detective Lee Scanlon in yet?

325
00:15:56,838 --> 00:15:58,711
Can I leave him a message?

326
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:00,103
My name's Allison Dubois.

327
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,534
Can you tell him
to meet me at the corner

328
00:16:01,613 --> 00:16:03,759
of Mesa and Pueblo at 12:30?

329
00:16:05,084 --> 00:16:06,173
Tell him
to look out for me.

330
00:16:06,237 --> 00:16:07,548
I'll be taking a cab.

331
00:16:08,237 --> 00:16:10,692
Mom, can I please
stay home from school?

332
00:16:11,244 --> 00:16:12,698
No. No, you cannot.

333
00:16:13,135 --> 00:16:15,134
And don't you dare
go to the nurse's office

334
00:16:15,198 --> 00:16:16,352
and make me come and get you.

335
00:16:16,399 --> 00:16:18,206
You will be grounded
the rest of eighth grade.

336
00:16:20,686 --> 00:16:22,165
Endorphins.

337
00:16:25,739 --> 00:16:26,763
Just so you know,
I was supposed to

338
00:16:26,861 --> 00:16:28,915
have lunch with a certain
someone who works for the Mayor.

339
00:16:29,172 --> 00:16:31,050
You may have to vouch for me
at a later date.

340
00:16:31,171 --> 00:16:32,730
Consider yourself vouched.

341
00:16:32,845 --> 00:16:34,027
Now, what is it
we're looking for?

342
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:35,881
In about one minute, a
man's gonna go through

343
00:16:35,945 --> 00:16:37,474
this traffic signal.

344
00:16:37,584 --> 00:16:39,105
There'll be a dead man
in the trunk of his car,

345
00:16:39,184 --> 00:16:42,712
along with about 100 rounds
of ammo, automatic weapon,

346
00:16:42,792 --> 00:16:45,512
not to mention blueprints
to a building downtown.

347
00:16:45,873 --> 00:16:47,616
If I'd driven
myself here today,

348
00:16:47,752 --> 00:16:50,087
I believe that he would've been
fated to run through the light

349
00:16:50,152 --> 00:16:51,543
and hit me with his car.

350
00:16:51,672 --> 00:16:53,263
But since I got
here early by cab,

351
00:16:54,104 --> 00:16:55,886
my hope is that he will
go through the light

352
00:16:55,919 --> 00:16:58,439
without incident, you will
arrest him and prevent him

353
00:16:58,494 --> 00:17:01,024
from whatever awful thing he
was bound and determined to do.

354
00:17:01,108 --> 00:17:02,021
You with me?

355
00:17:02,084 --> 00:17:03,612
And you know this
because...?

356
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:05,764
Because of the wonderful
things she does.

357
00:17:06,124 --> 00:17:07,595
That traffic light
right there?

358
00:17:08,688 --> 00:17:10,986
That light there.
Black sedan.

359
00:17:12,178 --> 00:17:13,247
Like that one.

360
00:17:13,392 --> 00:17:15,587
Oh, boy, I get to use my siren.

361
00:17:31,618 --> 00:17:32,541
Wait here.

362
00:17:46,603 --> 00:17:48,225
Well, this is
embarrassing.

363
00:17:49,009 --> 00:17:51,122
I ran a red light
back there, didn't I?

364
00:17:51,266 --> 00:17:52,473
You certainly did.

365
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:53,913
Your Honor.

366
00:18:15,143 --> 00:18:16,598
I don't understand.

367
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:20,854
I don't know
what to tell you.

368
00:18:20,909 --> 00:18:21,814
It's pretty
cut and dried.

369
00:18:21,856 --> 00:18:24,252
I just pulled over a
Federal Court Judge.

370
00:18:24,421 --> 00:18:25,685
A Federal Court Judge.

371
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:27,373
The Honorable
James T. Whitman.

372
00:18:27,493 --> 00:18:29,284
Nice fellow,
crappy golfer.

373
00:18:29,396 --> 00:18:30,307
What about his trunk?

374
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:31,948
I didn't see you
look in his trunk.

375
00:18:32,109 --> 00:18:33,955
That's 'cause I didn't
look in his trunk, Allison.

376
00:18:34,019 --> 00:18:35,244
He's a Federal
Court Judge.

377
00:18:35,308 --> 00:18:37,465
What part of Federal Court
Judge don't you understand?

378
00:18:37,571 --> 00:18:39,226
I'm not about to ask that
man to open his trunk

379
00:18:39,282 --> 00:18:40,842
when I have no
probable cause.

380
00:18:41,314 --> 00:18:42,257
The last time
I checked,

381
00:18:42,331 --> 00:18:44,336
your dreams do not
constitute probable cause.

382
00:18:54,113 --> 00:18:55,592
You want some lunch?

383
00:18:55,847 --> 00:18:57,192
I'll buy you lunch.

384
00:19:05,598 --> 00:19:06,601
Hello?

385
00:19:06,696 --> 00:19:09,044
This is Nurse Dunbar
down at Central Middle School.

386
00:19:09,165 --> 00:19:11,125
I've got Ariel here,

387
00:19:11,252 --> 00:19:13,659
and, please
don't be alarmed,

388
00:19:13,763 --> 00:19:15,653
but another child
here at the school

389
00:19:15,708 --> 00:19:18,085
has apparently given
Ariel a black eye.

390
00:19:18,172 --> 00:19:19,380
A black eye?

391
00:19:19,516 --> 00:19:20,710
We've got some ice on it,

392
00:19:20,748 --> 00:19:22,028
and I'm sure
in an hour or so

393
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:23,578
she'll be fine
to return to class.

394
00:19:23,892 --> 00:19:25,057
Oh, my God,
this is horrible.

395
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,737
Is she okay?
Can I talk to her?

396
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:34,101
Um, actually, um, she's laying
down at the moment, Mrs. Dubois.

397
00:19:34,402 --> 00:19:37,147
MAN (over radio):
All units in the vicinity...
I want to come pick her up.
Tell her I'll be right there.

398
00:19:37,419 --> 00:19:38,202
Thank you.

399
00:19:38,402 --> 00:19:39,970
...reporting a possible
hostage situation

400
00:19:40,006 --> 00:19:41,249
at the Florenzo Ristorante.

401
00:19:41,329 --> 00:19:42,858
I'm afraid you're not
going anywhere soon.

402
00:19:49,801 --> 00:19:50,529
I was in the
neighborhood,

403
00:19:50,649 --> 00:19:51,687
I heard you guys
were up to no good.

404
00:19:51,744 --> 00:19:53,417
JACKSON:
Well, somebody's
up to no good.

405
00:19:53,704 --> 00:19:54,897
About 35 minutes ago,

406
00:19:54,977 --> 00:19:57,176
911 got a call from inside
the restaurant about a robbery.

407
00:19:57,232 --> 00:20:00,039
When the first
responding officer arrived,

408
00:20:00,094 --> 00:20:01,519
the perpetrator
was still inside.

409
00:20:01,678 --> 00:20:04,103
He's holed up in there
with 57 hostages.

410
00:20:04,242 --> 00:20:05,261
How many?

411
00:20:05,431 --> 00:20:07,846
I've got sharpshooters on
all the surrounding rooftops.

412
00:20:08,070 --> 00:20:10,231
And the hostage negotiator
just got off the phone.

413
00:20:10,389 --> 00:20:12,182
What's he want?
What's he asking for?

414
00:20:12,269 --> 00:20:13,309
That's the fun part.

415
00:20:13,453 --> 00:20:14,485
He wants nothing.

416
00:20:14,525 --> 00:20:16,318
He's made no real demands.

417
00:20:16,413 --> 00:20:18,420
Just wants us to wait out here
till 5:00 p.m.

418
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:20,588
Then he'll release the hostages
and give back the money.

419
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:22,545
That makes no sense.
Tell me about it.

420
00:20:22,608 --> 00:20:24,520
Excuse me, Captain Jackson,
could you follow me?

421
00:20:30,710 --> 00:20:32,085
Lee.

422
00:20:32,776 --> 00:20:34,246
Take a look at that.

423
00:20:35,341 --> 00:20:36,806
Is that who I think it is?

424
00:20:36,924 --> 00:20:38,598
Man, this guy's really
pushing his luck.

425
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:40,111
A handicapped spot.

426
00:20:40,597 --> 00:20:41,717
I'm not imagining
it, right?

427
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:43,788
That's that
judge's car.

428
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,171
Well, I guess today
is not his lucky day.

429
00:20:47,811 --> 00:20:48,624
I don't know
what to do.

430
00:20:48,676 --> 00:20:49,594
I dreamt about
that car.

431
00:20:49,634 --> 00:20:52,483
Now that that car's here, I'd
kind of like to stay if I could.

432
00:20:52,921 --> 00:20:54,364
Let me go call
my husband.

433
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:04,577
MAN (over radio):
Central Command,
this is Watchtower. Over.

434
00:21:04,864 --> 00:21:05,960
I'm on the northeast corner

435
00:21:06,049 --> 00:21:07,864
of the roof of
the adjacent building.

436
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:10,440
From my vantage point, sir,
it appears someone is attempting

437
00:21:10,488 --> 00:21:13,271
to make their way out of the
rear entrance of the restaurant.

438
00:21:15,151 --> 00:21:15,912
It's a glass door,

439
00:21:15,991 --> 00:21:18,767
and I keep seeing them
approach it and then hesitate.

440
00:21:19,495 --> 00:21:20,975
To be honest, sir,
I don't know if I'm looking

441
00:21:21,054 --> 00:21:23,205
at a hostage
or the hostage taker.

442
00:21:23,798 --> 00:21:25,054
Can you describe him?

443
00:21:25,197 --> 00:21:27,494
Male, approximately
six-feet-tall,

444
00:21:27,621 --> 00:21:30,117
shirt and tie,
looks like he's got a mask on,

445
00:21:30,229 --> 00:21:32,500
carrying some kind of
blue gym bag.

446
00:21:33,436 --> 00:21:34,764
Judge Whitman.

447
00:21:35,292 --> 00:21:36,515
In my dream,

448
00:21:36,875 --> 00:21:39,388
there was a blue gym bag
in the trunk of the car,

449
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:41,147
along with the body,
along with the ammo,

450
00:21:41,205 --> 00:21:42,523
along with
an automatic weapon.

451
00:21:42,653 --> 00:21:44,443
Sir, I stopped
a suspicious-looking person

452
00:21:44,498 --> 00:21:46,499
matching that description
earlier today.

453
00:21:47,271 --> 00:21:48,376
He comes through the door

454
00:21:48,442 --> 00:21:50,319
and gives you any reason
to believe he's anything

455
00:21:50,354 --> 00:21:52,827
other than a hostage,
shoot to immobilize.

456
00:21:54,337 --> 00:21:55,473
MAN (over radio):
Here he comes.

457
00:21:56,504 --> 00:21:58,320
He's out.
He's got a weapon.

458
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,320
I'm taking my shot.

459
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:09,002
He's down.
Repeat. Man is down.

460
00:22:09,117 --> 00:22:10,869
He's just outside the rear
of the building.

461
00:22:20,188 --> 00:22:20,978
Sir.

462
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:23,307
I need you to
release your weapon.

463
00:22:32,394 --> 00:22:33,868
It's taped to him
or something.

464
00:22:51,531 --> 00:22:52,827
We shot the wrong guy.

465
00:22:59,916 --> 00:23:01,634
His-his gun jammed.

466
00:23:01,765 --> 00:23:03,010
It jammed.

467
00:23:04,129 --> 00:23:05,193
Judge Whitman...

468
00:23:05,681 --> 00:23:07,608
He taped this
gun to his hand, he...

469
00:23:07,722 --> 00:23:10,188
gave him that bag,
he pushed him out the back door.

470
00:23:10,273 --> 00:23:12,625
So he could leave out the front
with the rest of the hostages.

471
00:23:46,577 --> 00:23:48,495
Do you need help
deciding what to wear?

472
00:23:50,712 --> 00:23:53,400
It's clean.
It's absolutely clean.

473
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:55,456
What day is today?

474
00:23:55,912 --> 00:23:57,296
Mmm. Friday.

475
00:23:57,807 --> 00:23:59,111
Thank God.

476
00:24:00,518 --> 00:24:02,438
Wait...
I feel a hackneyed phrase

477
00:24:02,494 --> 00:24:03,839
coming on.

478
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:05,717
It passed.

479
00:24:06,550 --> 00:24:09,950
Okay, but why would a
federal judge do that?

480
00:24:10,070 --> 00:24:11,076
Rob a restaurant?

481
00:24:11,182 --> 00:24:12,989
Hold hostages?
I don't know.

482
00:24:13,092 --> 00:24:14,420
He's not doing it for the money.

483
00:24:14,508 --> 00:24:16,884
He sends the money out
with one of the hostages.

484
00:24:18,284 --> 00:24:19,924
Assuming any of this is real.

485
00:24:20,003 --> 00:24:21,308
Assuming any of this

486
00:24:21,403 --> 00:24:24,076
is actually going
to happen, I mean...

487
00:24:24,115 --> 00:24:25,700
it was just a dream.

488
00:24:26,946 --> 00:24:28,339
What?

489
00:24:28,505 --> 00:24:30,937
No, just... I love
that you said that.

490
00:24:30,994 --> 00:24:33,049
I mean, normally I'd
be the one to say that.

491
00:24:33,532 --> 00:24:34,577
Yeah.

492
00:24:34,681 --> 00:24:36,466
Well, it just occurred to me
when I woke up,

493
00:24:36,521 --> 00:24:39,594
when I realized that my jacket
wasn't covered with blood.

494
00:24:39,682 --> 00:24:41,929
None of what I had dreamt
had happened.

495
00:24:42,097 --> 00:24:44,287
I felt relief.
I still feel relief.

496
00:24:44,592 --> 00:24:46,577
Excellent.
Relief is good.

497
00:24:47,088 --> 00:24:47,965
You know,

498
00:24:48,011 --> 00:24:49,151
it's hard to explain it.

499
00:24:49,436 --> 00:24:53,018
Every time I dream the dream,
there are certain cues.

500
00:24:53,131 --> 00:24:55,719
There are certain things
that happen at the start.

501
00:24:55,799 --> 00:24:56,884
But this morning...

502
00:24:56,972 --> 00:24:58,305
the fact that
the kids aren't up,

503
00:24:58,363 --> 00:25:00,201
the fact that we're up early.

504
00:25:00,929 --> 00:25:02,475
This is different.

505
00:25:02,593 --> 00:25:04,922
Gee, we are up kind of early.

506
00:25:07,775 --> 00:25:10,175
Hey, here's a crazy idea.

507
00:25:11,799 --> 00:25:15,160
How about we go back
to bed and not sleep.

508
00:25:15,655 --> 00:25:16,792
Hmm?

509
00:25:20,558 --> 00:25:21,975
Was that a "no"?

510
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:22,896
Yeah.

